[1]DescrizioneL'the acanthus is a herbaceous perennial plant that can reach a height of 1.5 m.
[2]The leaves have a long petiole and robust, and a lamina bright green; they are of the form pennatifida with lobes deeply cut-toothed.
[3]The drum is floriferous (port i.e. the flowers directly on it).
[4]The flowers are collected in long spikes terminals to form cylindrical; they are rather showy for the chromatic contrast between the corolla (white in color with shades of pale pink) and the cup (red-purple).
Diagonal:2, Size:3
[6]The fruits are capsules loculicide bivalve opening explosive.
[7]The seeds are rather big and smooth, color brownish-black.
[9]Distribution and habitatL'acanthus is popular in the mediterranean region, western and central; its area extends from west Africa to Croatia and also Portugal.
